===Etymology 1===
{{bor|en|fr|bergamote}}, from {{der|en|it|bergamotta}}, from {{der|en|ota|[[بك]] [[آرمود|آرمودی]]|tr=beg armudu|lit=a lord's pear}}, denoting a [[w:de:Bergamotte (Birne)|fattish kind of pear]]. The European word developed the sense of a fruit of a certain citrus cultivar in the late 17th century.

